creator: Daniel Defoe
description:
LibriVox recording of Aventuras de Robinsón Crusoe by Daniel Defoe. (Translated by Jean Labouderie; José Alegret de Mesa).

Read in Spanish by Joyfull; Mongope; Ditirambo; Ana Núñez Ronchi; Charbelí Ramos Chávez; Tux; and Victor Villarraza.

Robinson Crusoe, único superviviente de un naufragio, es arrastrado por las olas a la playa de una isla desierta. Robinson, confiando en su ingenio, hará de todo para poder sobrevivir. Pero un día descubre que no está completamente solo en la isla... (Tux)

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
